{"votes": {"funny": 0, "useful": 0, "cool": 0}, "user_id": "wUnFHMs9kWIPzm7uEnRAKQ", "review_id": "bouf_rlO1mn9rfiyc6GUig", "text": "although this place has been open since the summer, i only recently tried it out and i must say i am impressed. i have had bibimbap before but not quite like this. i got the beef bibimbap and the seafood pancake, both were delicious. the bibimbap was served in a stone bowl, this was very unique as i have never eaten a full meal out of a stone bowl before. it was also very convenient for keeping the food warm throughout the meal. it came with beef, rice, spinach, mushroom, kimchee, green onions and the other standard veggies that come along with bibimbap. although in my previous experience it always came with an egg, this was not the case at bibigo. you have a selection of hot sauces to choose from, i got the hottest of course and it also came with a pouch of sesame oil, a very nice addition to the meal. you mix it all together yourself. the seafood pancake was essentially egg pancake encrusted with scallops, shrimp, green onions, and small bits of squid. it also came with its own dipping sauce and a side of kimchee. both things together was around $18, it may seem expensive if you view bibigo as a fast food or takeout eatery but you can in fact have a sit down dinner with full waiter service if you so choose which in that case $18 seems like a steal. i highly recommend this place.", "business_id": "SZHJsSqbIpURYPXtKkrF7g", "stars": 4, "date": "2010-10-11", "type": "review"}